  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nExclusive to:\nRain Hat\n\"Soft to the touch, slick to the rain.\"\nObject Info\nPerk\nProtects from Rain and Lightning.\nEquipable\n10 days\nRepaired By Sewing\nDoes not stack\nProtection\n70% resistance\nCrafting\n×2 ×1 ×1\nFilters\nTier\nMiscellaneous\n\"rainhat\"\n“It'll mess up my hair, but I'll stay nice and dry.”\n–Wilson\n“Anything to keep the water away.”\n–Willow\n“Is like water off mole's back.”\n–Wolfgang\n“What fun is rain if you're not getting wet?”\n–Wendy\n“INSULATED PROTECTION FROM WATER DAMAGE”\n–WX-78\n“I hate when my bun gets wet.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Always keep a dry head while chopping.”\n–Woodie\n“Not the most dapper of hats, but quite necessary.”\n–Maxwell\n“We will fight in the rain.”\n–Wigfrid\n“It'll keep the water out of our fur.”\n–Webber\n“Better than a newspaper.”\n–Warly\n“Looks good?”\n–Wormwood\n“Dry as a daisy. That's the phrase, right?”\n–Winona\n“Splish and splash!”\n–Wortox\n“Rain not scary!”\n–Wurt\n“I wonder if I could make one for Woby too.”\n–Walter\n“What a charming rain bonnet!”\n–Wanda\nThe Rain Hat is a craftable Dress item from the Reign of Giants DLC. It requires 2 Moleworms, 1 Straw Hat, and 1 Bone Shard to craft and an Alchemy Engine to prototype. The Sewing Kit repairs 50% of its durability.\nWhen worn during Rain, it protects against Wetness gain by 70%. Additionally, it insulates the player against Lightning strikes and the electric shocks of a charged Volt Goat.\nContents\n1 Skins\n2 Trivia\n3 Assets\n4 Gallery\nSkins[edit | edit source]\nMain article: Belongings\nCowboy Rain Hat\n(associated with: )\nRain Bonnet\nA dear little bonnet to keep your head dry.\n(associated with: )\nFloppy Rain Hat\n(associated with: )\nLooks Like Rain Hat\nKeep your noggin dry!\n(associated with: )\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nRain Hats require Moleworms to craft because the moleskin is known for its water-resistance.\nThe crafting recipe used to require Tentacle Spots instead of Moleworms.\nWearing this hat while standing under Tree provides sufficient Wetness protection from rain.\nAssets[edit | edit source]\nRain HatCowboy Rain HatRain BonnetFloppy Rain HatLooks Like Rain Hat\nDropped\nEquipped\nDropped\nEquipped\nDropped\nEquipped\nDropped\nEquipped\nDropped\nEquipped\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nThe Rain Hat as seen in the Hook, Line, and Inker trailer.\nWilson with a Rain Hat in Reign of Giants spring promo poster\nWilson wearing a Rain Hat.\nWillow wearing a Rain Hat.\nWolfgang wearing a Rain Hat.\nWendy wearing a Rain Hat.\nWX-78 wearing a Rain Hat.\nWickerbottom wearing a Rain Hat.\nWoodie wearing a Rain Hat.\nWes wearing a Rain Hat.\nMaxwell wearing a Rain Hat.\nWigfrid wearing a Rain Hat.\nWebber wearing a Rain Hat.\nWalani wearing a Rain Hat.\nWarly wearing a Rain Hat.\nWilbur wearing a Rain Hat.\nWoodlegs wearing a Rain Hat.\nWilba wearing a Rain Hat.\nWormwood wearing a Rain Hat.\nWheeler wearing a Rain Hat.\nWinona wearing a Rain Hat.\nWortox wearing a Rain Hat.\nWurt wearing a Rain Hat.\nTools and WeaponsCraftable Items\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Tools and Weapons\nEquipped Tools\nUnequipped Tools\nLight\nBooks\nCircuits\nBattle Calls\nWatches\nWeapons\nSlingshot Parts\nThrowables\nStaffs\nAmulets\nBackpacks\nClothing\nStage Costumes\nArmor\nDSTDSRoGSWHam\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Craftable Items\nRegular Filters\nSurvivor Items\nWilson\nWillow\nWolfgang\nWendy\nWX-78\nWickerbottom\nWoodie\nWes\nMaxwell\nWigfrid\nWebber\nWarly\nWortox\nWormwood\nWinona\nWurt\nWalter\nWanda\nTools\nLight Sources\nPrototypers & Stations\nRefined Materials\nWeapons\nArmor\nClothing\nHealing\nMagic\nDecorations\nStructures\nStorage Solutions\nCooking\nFood & Gardening\nFishing\nSeafaring\nBeefalo Riding\nWinter Items\nSummer Items\nRain Gear\nCrafting Station Filters\nSpecial Event\nAncient Pseudoscience\nCarpentry\nCartography\nCritters\nCelestial\nBrightsmithy\nShadowcraft\nFabrication\nBottle Exchange\nCombrining Filt