  "summaryViHtml": "<h2>Tóm tắt</h2><p>Mũ Mưa là một Trang Phục có thể chế tạo được từ DLC Reign of Giants. Nó cần 2 Giun Chũi, 1 Mũ Rơm và 1 Mảnh Xương để chế tạo và Máy Luyện Kim để tạo nguyên mẫu. Bộ May vá sửa chữa 50% độ bền của nó.</p>",
  "title": "Rain Hat/DST",
  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Exclusivity|Reign of Giants|Shipwrecked|Hamlet|Don't Starve Together}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|equipslot=head\n|image = Rain Hat Dropped.png\n|icon = Rain Hat.png\n|ingredient1 = Moleworm\n|multiplier1 = 2\n|ingredient2 = Straw Hat\n|multiplier2 = 1\n|ingredient3 = Bone Shards\n|multiplier3 = 1\n|filter = {{Pic32|Clothing Filter}} {{Pic32|Rain Gear Filter}}\n|tier = 2\n|perk = Protects from [[Rain]] and [[Lightning]].\n|stack = Does not stack\n|spawnCode = \"rainhat\"\n|wearsOut = 10 days\n|repaired_by_sewing=1\n|waterResistance = 70% resistance\n|description = Soft to the touch, slick to the rain.}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson=It'll mess up my hair, but I'll stay nice and dry.\n|willow=Anything to keep the water away.\n|wolfgang=Is like water off mole's back.\n|wendy=What fun is rain if you're not getting wet?\n|wx78=INSULATED PROTECTION FROM WATER DAMAGE\n|wickerbottom=I hate when my bun gets wet.\n|woodie=Always keep a dry head while chopping.\n|maxwell=Not the most dapper of hats, but quite necessary.\n|wigfrid=We will fight in the rain.\n|webber=It'll keep the water out of our fur.\n|warly=Better than a newspaper.\n|wormwood=Looks good?\n|winona=Dry as a daisy. That's the phrase, right?\n|wortox=Splish and splash!\n|wurt = Rain not scary!\n|walter = I wonder if I could make one for Woby too.\n|wanda = What a charming rain bonnet!\n|choose=wilson}}\nThe '''Rain Hat''' is a craftable [[Dress]] item from the ''[[Don't Starve: Reign of Giants|Reign of Giants]]'' DLC. It requires 2 [[Moleworm]]s, 1 [[Straw Hat]], and 1 [[Bone Shards|Bone Shard]] to craft and an [[Alchemy Engine]] to prototype. The [[Sewing Kit]] repairs 50% of its durability.\n\nWhen worn during [[Rain]], it protects against [[Wetness]] gain by 70%. Additionally, it insulates the player against [[Lightning]] strikes and the electric shocks of a charged [[Volt Goat]].\n\n== [[File:Skins Icon.png|32px|link=]] Skins ==\n<noinclude>{{Main|Belongings#Head_items|Belongings}}</noinclude>\n<div style=\"display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; justify-content: center;\">\n{{SkinInfo\n|image = Cowboy Straw Hat - Rain Hat Icon.png\n|name = Cowboy Rain Hat\n|associated = Cowboy Straw Hat Icon.png\n}}\n{{SkinInfo\n|image = Rain Bonnet - Rain Hat Icon.png\n|name = Rain Bonnet\n|description = A dear little bonnet to keep your head dry.\n|associated = Straw Bonnet Icon.png\n}}\n{{SkinInfo\n|image = Floppy Straw Hat - Rain Hat Icon.png\n|name = Floppy Rain Hat\n|associated = Floppy Straw Hat Icon.png\n}}\n{{SkinInfo\n|image = Looks Like Rain Hat Icon.png\n|name = Looks Like Rain Hat\n|description = Keep your noggin dry!\n|associated = Rancher Straw Hat Icon.png\n}}\n</div>\n\n== {{Pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* Rain Hats require [[Moleworm]]s to craft because the moleskin is known for its water-resistance.\n* The crafting recipe used to require [[Tentacle Spot]]s instead of Moleworms.\n* Wearing this hat while standing under [[Tree]] provides sufficient Wetness protection from rain.\n{{clear}}\n\n== {{Pic32|Research Notes}} Assets ==\n<tabber>\nRain Hat=\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nRain Hat Dropped.png|Dropped\nRain Hat Equipped.png| Equipped\n</gallery>\n|-|\nCowboy Rain Hat=\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nCowboy Rain Hat Dropped.png|Dropped\nCowboy Rain Hat Equipped.png| Equipped\n</gallery>\n|-|\nRain Bonnet=\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nRain Bonnet Dropped.png|Dropped\nRain Bonnet Equipped.png| Equipped\n</gallery>\n|-|\nFloppy Rain Hat=\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nFloppy Rain Hat Dropped.png|Dropped\nFloppy Rain Hat Equipped.png| Equipped\n</gallery>\n|-|\nLooks Like Rain Hat=\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nLooks Like Rain Hat Dropped.png|Dropped\nLooks Like Rain Hat Equipped.png| Equipped\n</gallery>\n</tabber>\n\n== {{Pic32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nDST Hook Line and Inker Trailer Wilson.png|The Rain Hat as seen in the ''Hook, Line, and Inker'' trailer.\nFile:Spring RoG poster.png|Wilson with a Rain Hat in Reign of Giants spring promo poster\nRain Hat Wilson.png|[[Wilson]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Willow.png|[[Willow]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wolfgang.png|[[Wolfgang]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wendy.png|[[Wendy]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat WX-78.png|[[WX-78]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wickerbottom.png|[[Wickerbottom]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Woodie.png|[[Woodie]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wes.png|[[Wes]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Maxwell.png|[[Maxwell (character)|Maxwell]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wigfrid.png|[[Wigfrid]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Webber.png|[[Webber]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Walani.png|[[Walani]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Warly.png|[[Warly]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wilbur.png|[[Wilbur]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Woodlegs.png|[[Woodlegs]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wilba.png|[[Wilba]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wormwood.png|[[Wormwood]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wheeler.png|[[Wheeler]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Winona.png|[[Winona]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wortox.png|[[Wortox]] wearing a Rain Hat.\nRain Hat Wurt.png|[[Wurt]] wearing a Rain Hat.\n</gallery>\n<tabber>\nTools and Weapons=\n{{Tools and Weapons}}\n|-|\nCraftable Items=\n{{Craftable Items|tool}}\n</tabber>\n[[fr:Chapeau de pluie]]\n[[Category:Reign of Giants]]\n[[Category:Hats]]\n[[Category:Craftable Items]]\n[[Category:Clothing Filter]]\n[[Category:Rain Gear Filter]]\n[[Category:Water Resistant]]\n[[Category:Equipable Items]]\n[[Category:Science]]\n[[Category:Limited use]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]\n[[Category:Shock Resistant]]"
